{"id": "duc04-testb-24:1#4", "contents": "The Camp David accords were not signed until September 17, 1978, about five weeks before that year's peace prize was announced. Although the committee could not give Carter the prize, they recognized his efforts in the 1978 awards citation, stating \"the positive initiative taken by President Jimmy Carter.\" Lundestad revealed that the committee had tried to find a loophole in the rules, which are overseen by the Swedish Nobel Foundation. However, Stig Ramel, the then-director of the Nobel Foundation, advised against breaking the rules, citing a matter of principle."}
